# Sketchbook Learning Notes Rule

When creating or editing learning notes in this repository:

1. Use a visual-first style:
   - section cards
   - short bullets
   - connector arrows/flow strips
   - checklist callouts
2. Keep prose concise and avoid large paragraphs.
3. Follow:
   - `docs/sketchbook-style-guide.md`
   - `docs/system-design-note-template.md`
   - `docs/content-workflow.md`
4. Ensure each note includes:
   - clear learning goal
   - component breakdown
   - end-to-end flow
   - reliability/security/operations perspective
   - key takeaways
5. Maintain a handwritten/sketchbook tone while preserving technical accuracy.
